The paper proposes new methods to speed up convergence of the Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM), which is a common optimization tool in the context of large scale and distributed learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), distributed computing (cs.DC), control systems (cs.SY), and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
